The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 0.2 percent to 22,697.16. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  was little changed at 2,858.44.  Industrial and mining shares gained after U.S. stocks and
commodities advanced, said Leoncio Altamirano, a trader at Lima-
based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peruâ€™s largest zinc
and silver producer, rose 2.1 percent to 4.90 soles.  Sociedad
Minera Cerro Verde SA (SMCV)  (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan
Copper & Gold Inc., climbed 2.1 percent to $38.78.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
gained 1.8 percent to 2.78 soles after raising $60 million from
a share sale.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian
exploration company, advanced 1.8 percent to $1.13.  Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POM\C)  (POMALCC1 PE), a sugar producer, rose
1.6 percent to 65 centimos after futures gained for the fourth
session in five in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
